This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not reprinted without permission

By Li Yulou, southern weekend correspondent

Southern weekend intern, Gong Roushan

Editor in chief | Wu Xiaoyu

On January 20,2020, five days after the onset of symptoms such as cough and weakness, the post-80s patient Zhang Qing was admitted to Huanggang City Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine after two rounds of blood clots and a CT scan, during which he stayed in a hotel near the hospital, separate yourself from your family.

Before this day, the pneumonia about the COVID-19 infection had appeared, but did not get much attention, Zhang Qing's diagnosis in the book is the diagnosis of "viral pneumonia. ".

"The hospital had no beds until now, and the second CT showed that the inflammation in the lungs was quite serious, so the doctors managed to arrange a bed, " Zhang Qing's wife told southern weekend by telephone on the evening of January 23, the husband had a nucleic acid test that day and is still waiting for the results.

The nucleic acid test is an important step in identifying COVID-19 pneumonia, but hospitals in the cities around Wuhan had not previously been able to get a test kit, objectively, no confirmed cases have been reported in these cities.

"As of January 19, the number of cases in Huanggang has reached 109, " said Zhan Caihong, head of the Qichun County People's government, who was quoted by Caixin as saying at the county's viral pneumonia conference on January 20, it was not until January 21 that the first 12 confirmed cases were reported in Huanggang.

"The first batch of nucleic acid kits was obtained in Huanggang on the evening of the 19th. The testing process took two days and the number of kits was limited. The first batch was mainly distributed to designated hospitals in the main urban area, " a doctor from the fever clinic of the Central Huanggang Hospital told southern weekend, he was informed of an unexplained pneumonia in Wuhan on December 31,2019, and of a suspected case in Huanggang on January 10,2020, according to a document posted online by the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission.

On the morning of January 25, Huanggang reported 52 new cases, the second time Huanggang had reported new cases, after Huanggang became the first city outside Wuhan to report a confirmed case.

At 2400 hours on January 23, Huanggang suspended buses, long-distance passenger traffic and departures from train stations, hours after several cities, including Ezhou and Xiantao, closed the city.

At present, the Huanggang Huangzhou, Tuanfeng County, Qichun County, Huangmei and other districts and counties designated medical institutions have a shortage of isolation beds, fever clinics have also increased significantly, mild patients will be advised to isolation treatment at home.

On the evening of January 24, several medical and nursing staff at Qichun County People's Hospital all told the southern weekend reporter by telephone that the hospital received a small amount of test kits on the afternoon of the 23rd, and that the patients identified by the expert group as highly suspected could be tested, but still need to report the results of the provincial and municipal levels of disease control before the announcement of a diagnosis.

1
A week against the enemy

1

###A week against the enemy

Zhang has no recent travel history in the city, which he last visited in October 2019 and has been in downtown Huanggang ever since. On 15 January 2020, he felt unwell and went to Huanggang Chinese Medicine Hospital for examination the next day after developing fever.

"At that time, the hospital was already facing the enemy. Even though there was no isolation ward, the hospital opened a floor to admit suspected patients, with an estimated 50 to 60 beds. " Zhang Qing's wife told southern weekend reporters that after blood tests and films, the doctor learned that Zhang Qing recently did not go to Wuhan, suggested that its first home isolation observation, a few days later and a CT to see the situation.

Three days later, he was found to have obvious difficulty breathing, and again went to the Chinese hospital for examination, this time viral pneumonia by the doctor, who ordered him to isolate himself and wait in line for a bed. By the morning of January 20, Zhang Qing had moved from the hotel next to the hospital into the hospital's newly opened respiratory ward.

"At that time, it was not called an isolation ward, but the doctor would tell the nursing family the risks and advise them to take adequate precautions, but there were still a small half of the family members who did not wear a mask, " Zhang's wife said.

On Jan. 20, the day Zhang Qing moved into the hospital, there was a surge in confirmed cases in Wuhan. Since then, the atmosphere in the ward has become tense and there has been a marked reduction in the number of nursing families, with almost no one without a mask.

Medical staff at Huanggang City Center Hospital told southern weekend, "Huanggang received the first batch of kits on the evening of the 19th. The testing process took two days and there were only a limited number of kits. The first batch was mainly distributed to designated hospitals in the main urban area. "

Zhang Qing's wife, who learned the news, asked her attending doctor if she could have a nucleic acid test to confirm the diagnosis, "My doctor told me that the number of kits was very limited and that they could only be distributed according to the degree of suspicion, and that patients in TCM hospitals had relatively mild conditions. My doctor reassured me that the diagnosis and treatment were similar. "

Zhang and his wife trust the doctor's judgment, and now they are waiting for the results of the nucleic acid test.

Information obtained by southern weekend journalists showed that there was a suspected infection among medical staff at Huanggang's Central Hospital before the quarantine zone was opened.

On January 17, Xu Hui, a doctor at an eye hospital in Huanggang, received a call from a friend at the Central Hospital. "He told me to put on a mask, I asked a few questions before I knew it was the staff at the Central Hospital who had the infection. "

The 12 confirmed cases in Huanggang included five health care workers, including a doctor and four nurses, according to a 21-day bulletin. The above-mentioned center hospital doctor confirmed to the southern weekend reporter, 5 cases of confirmed medical staff from the hospital. The hospital's first suspected case of infection staff appeared on January 10, is a registered clerk.

In fact, since then the hospital has been like the enemy, prevention and control upgrade, but the home in the central hospital near the Lin Shan did not feel the slightest. Lam returned to Huanggang from abroad on January 18, when there was nothing unusual in downtown Huanggang and no one wearing a mask could be seen on the street.

Until the afternoon of January 20, Lin Shan went to the Central Hospital pharmacy across from the pharmacy to buy drugs found the pharmacy clerk wearing a mask, the next day on the street only sporadic pedestrians wearing masks.

On the morning of January 24, southern weekend learned from the medical staff of Huanggang's Central Hospital that the hospital was now able to test for nucleic acid reagents and suggested that suspected patients go to its fever clinic for diagnosis. Two other sentinel fever clinics in Huanggang have temporarily been unable to test for nucleic acid reagents.

According to a report in people on January 23, at least 100,000 kits have been produced by the first batch of approved manufacturers, while there are only over 1,000 confirmed cases, and there is an unusual shortage of kits on the front lines of hospitals, transport and distribution bottlenecks.

"The kits are mainly distributed by all levels of disease control, and early detection and diagnosis are completed by disease control. In recent days, some top three hospitals have been authorized, but the test results still need to be reported by provincial disease control experts to be confirmed and released, " said the doctors of the hospitals.

2
County hospitals are under pressure

2

###County hospitals are under pressure

The earlier suspected cases had a clear history of exposure in Wuhan.

On January 14, several members of a Tuanfeng County delegation to the meeting in Wuhan returned, and two of the patients were classified as critically ill.

In the days that followed, some of the patients recovered and were discharged, but several caregivers developed symptoms and were diagnosed as "viral pneumonia. ". "The patient's condition is still unstable and he has been told he can not test for nucleic acid reagent, " a family member told southern weekend

Huanggang Huanggang is the nearest district and county from Wuhan, Tuanfeng County Epidemic Prevention Headquarters told reporters at the weekend 24, Tuanfeng County, there are no confirmed cases, can not provide the number of suspected cases.

Southern weekend reporters learned from the isolation ward of Tuanfeng County People's Hospital that there are more than 40 patients in the isolation ward of the hospital. From the 23rd, some wards began to add beds.

The gap between "undiagnosed cases" and "multiple quarantined patients" is also largely due to the availability of kits and testing rights.

A medical staff member at the Tuanfeng County People's Hospital also told southern weekend on the morning of the 24th that the isolation beds in the hospital were very tight at present, and could only give priority to patients with severe illness. Patients with mild symptoms were advised to self-isolate at home. "undiagnosed patients are more likely to get cross-infection in a quarantined ward. "

Qichun County, which previously reported 11 suspected cases, has also seen a surge in cases. There are three designated hospitals in the county, the largest number in the counties under Huanggang, but there is a shortage of beds and medical supplies such as protective clothing and goggles to ensure the safety of medical staff.

A medical staff member at Qichun County People's Hospital told southern weekend on January 24 that the hospital had treated its first patient suspected of being infected with COVID-19 two weeks ago, and that the number of fever cases had surged on the 21st, on the afternoon of the 23rd, the nucleic acid kit for diagnosis was obtained, "but the quantity is very limited" .

At the request of the interviewee, Zhang Qing and Lin Shan were assumed names
